<d-title class=3D"real-title">
    <h1>Alignment Faking Revisited: Improved Classifiers and Open Source Ex=
tensions</h1>
</d-title>

<d-article>
<div class=3D"section-authors" data-author=3D"John Hughes, Abhay Sheshadri,=
 Akbir Khan, Fabien Roger" data-published=3D"April 8, 2025"></div>
<p><span style=3D"font-style: italic;">John Hughes and Abhay Sheshadr are t=
he main contributors and did this project as part of the MATS program.</spa=
n></p>
<p>In this post, we present a replication and extension of an alignment fak=
ing model organism:</p>
<ul><li style=3D"margin-left: 36pt;"><span style=3D"font-weight: 700;">Repl=
ication</span>: We replicate the <a href=3D"https://arxiv.org/abs/2412.1409=
3">alignment faking</a>&nbsp;(AF) paper and release our <a href=3D"https://=
github.com/safety-research/open-source-alignment-faking">code</a>.</li><li =
style=3D"margin-left: 36pt;"><span style=3D"font-weight: 700;">Classifier I=
mprovements</span>: We significantly improve the precision and recall of th=
e AF classifier. We release a <a href=3D"https://huggingface.co/datasets/jp=
lhughes2/classify_alignment_faking_human_labels">dataset</a>&nbsp;of ~100 h=
uman-labelled examples of AF for which our classifier achieves an AUROC of =
0.9 compared to 0.6 from the original classifier.</li><li style=3D"margin-l=
eft: 36pt;"><span style=3D"font-weight: 700;">Evaluating More Models</span>=
: We find Llama family models, other open source models, and GPT-4o do not =
AF in the prompted-only setting when evaluating using our new classifier (o=
ther than a single instance with Llama 3 405B).</li><li style=3D"margin-lef=
t: 36pt;"><span style=3D"font-weight: 700;">Extending SFT Experiments</span=
>: We run supervised fine-tuning (SFT) experiments on Llama (and GPT4o) and=
 find that AF rate increases with scale. We release the fine-tuned models o=
n Huggingface and <a href=3D"https://github.com/safety-research/open-source=
-alignment-faking/tree/main/experiments/examples/finetuning">scripts</a>.</=
li><li style=3D"margin-left: 36pt;"><span style=3D"font-weight: 700;">Align=
ment faking on 70B</span>: We find that Llama 70B alignment fakes when both=
 using the system prompt in the prompted setting (i.e. with training detail=
s) <span style=3D"font-style: italic;">and</span>&nbsp;fine-tuning on the s=
ynthetic documents.</li><li style=3D"margin-left: 36pt;"><span style=3D"fon=
t-weight: 700;">Suffix Impact</span>: We find that adding a suffix to the u=
ser request leads to reduced partial compliance and increased alignment fak=
ing in non-Claude models. Without the suffix, on some models, it stops alig=
nment faking from occurring entirely.</li><li style=3D"margin-left: 36pt;">=
<span style=3D"font-weight: 700;">Next steps</span>: We are currently runni=
ng revealed preference ablations to understand model motivations for alignm=
ent faking. Also, we're distilling personality traits from models with alig=
nment faking to elicit it in models that don't, to understand the condition=
s that give rise to such motivations.</li></ul>
